# API origin (no trailing slash). In local dev, omit this to use http://127.0.0.1:3000 (see getApiBaseUrl).
# Set explicitly if the API is not on port 3000, e.g. VITE_API_URL=http://127.0.0.1:4000
# Never set this to the backoffice URL (same as the Vite app) — uploads and admin calls will 404.
# In production, set to your API origin, e.g. https://api.example.com
# VITE_API_URL=

# On bloom-at-work-api, add this app origin to CORS_ORIGINS when calling the API from another port
# (e.g. http://localhost:8081,http://localhost:8083).
# Sign-in uses the same hub flow: POST /auth/login on the API (email + password); no separate backoffice env credentials.
